<doc id="902108" wikidata="Q7428426" url="?curid=902108" title="Savoy Bearcats">
<text>The Savoy Bearcats were an eleven-piece jazz band, led by Leon Abbey, which was the house band at the Savoy Ballroom in New York City from its opening in 1926 to 1928. The band&#x27;s name was changed from the Charleston Bearcats while they were at the Savoy. After leaving the Savoy they became known as Leon Abbey&#x27;s Band.

The band&#x27;s drummer was Tiny Bradshaw and its bassist was Ralph Escudero.

